---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/PageHero.astro";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
import { business } from "../data/site";
import { seoFor } from "../data/seo.generated";

const meta = seoFor("/privacy-policy/");
const title = meta?.title ?? "Privacy Policy | Mex Landscaping";
const description = meta?.description ?? "Mex Landscaping privacy policy.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description} path="/privacy-policy/" noindex>
  <PageHero title="Privacy Policy" crumbs={[{ label: "Home", href: "/" }, { label: "Privacy Policy" }]} />
  <Section>
    <div class="prose-mex mx-auto max-w-2xl">
      <p>Last updated: July 16, 2026</p>
      <p>
        {business.legalName} (“we”, “us”, “our”) respects your privacy. This
        policy explains what information we collect through our website, our
        advertising, and our contact channels, how we use it, how we share it,
        and the choices you have. By using our website or submitting a form,
        or by contacting us by phone or text, you agree to this policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Information we collect</h2>
      <p>We collect information in the following ways:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>
          <strong>Information you submit directly.</strong> When you complete a
          contact or estimate form on our website, we collect the details you
          provide, typically your name, phone number, email address, and
          information about your project and timeline.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Facebook and Instagram lead forms.</strong> When you respond
          to one of our advertisements on Facebook or Instagram and submit a
          lead form, Meta provides us the information you chose to share through
          that form, such as your name, phone number, and email address. That
          information is transferred into our customer management system so we
          can follow up with you. Meta’s own handling of your data is governed
          by Meta’s privacy policy.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Phone and text communications.</strong> When you call or text
          us, or when you give us your number, we collect your phone number and
          the contents of your communications so we can respond and provide our
          services.
        </li>
        <li>
          <strong>Information collected automatically.</strong> When you visit
          our website, we and our analytics providers automatically collect
          standard technical data such as your IP address, browser type, pages
          viewed, and referring source, using cookies and similar technologies.
        </li>
      </ul>

      <h2>How we use your information</h2>
      <ul>
        <li>To respond to inquiries, provide quotes, and schedule estimates</li>
        <li>To provide, perform, and improve our landscaping services</li>
        <li>To communicate with you about your project by phone, email, and text message</li>
        <li>To send you appointment reminders, follow-ups, and occasional offers you have consented to receive</li>
        <li>To measure and improve the performance of our website and advertising</li>
        <li>To comply with our legal obligations and enforce our agreements</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>Text messaging (SMS) and consent</h2>
      <p>
        By providing your phone number through one of our forms, a Facebook or
        Instagram lead form, or directly to our team, you consent to receive
        calls and text messages from {business.legalName} at that number,
        including messages sent using automated technology, about your inquiry,
        your project, appointment reminders, and related offers. Consent to
        receive marketing text messages is not a condition of purchasing any
        services.
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Message frequency varies. Message and data rates may apply.</li>
        <li>You can opt out of text messages at any time by replying <strong>STOP</strong>. You may reply <strong>HELP</strong> for help.</li>
        <li>Opting out of text messages will not remove you from phone or email contact unless you also ask us to stop those.</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        <strong>
          We do not sell, rent, or share your mobile phone number or your SMS
          consent with third parties or affiliates for their own marketing
          purposes.
        </strong>
      </p>

      <h2>Cookies and analytics</h2>
      <p>
        Our website uses Google Tag Manager and Google Analytics to understand
        how visitors use the site so we can improve it. These tools set cookies
        and collect usage data as described above. You can control cookies
        through your browser settings, and you can opt out of Google Analytics
        using Google’s browser add-on. If we run advertising through Meta or
        Google, those platforms may also use cookies or similar technologies to
        measure and target ads.
      </p>

      <h2>How we share information</h2>
      <p>
        We do not sell your personal information. We share it only as needed to
        operate our business, with trusted service providers who process it on
        our behalf, including:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Our website form and notification tools</li>
        <li>Our customer relationship and messaging platform (which sends email and text messages on our behalf)</li>
        <li>Advertising and analytics platforms such as Meta and Google</li>
        <li>Professional advisors, or authorities where required by law</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        These providers are permitted to use your information only to provide
        services to us, not for their own purposes.
      </p>

      <h2>Data retention</h2>
      <p>
        We keep your information for as long as needed to respond to your
        request, provide our services, and meet legal, tax, and record-keeping
        requirements. You may ask us to delete your information as described
        below.
      </p>

      <h2>Your choices and rights</h2>
      <p>
        You may ask us to access, correct, or delete the personal information we
        hold about you, and you may opt out of marketing calls, emails, or texts
        at any time. To make a request, contact us using the details below.
        Depending on where you live, you may have additional rights under
        applicable privacy laws.
      </p>

      <h2>Third-party links</h2>
      <p>
        Our website and ads may link to third-party sites and platforms we do
        not control. This policy does not apply to those sites, and we encourage
        you to review their privacy policies.
      </p>

      <h2>Children’s privacy</h2>
      <p>
        Our services and website are intended for adults. We do not knowingly
        collect personal information from children under 13.
      </p>

      <h2>Changes to this policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this policy from time to time. When we do, we will revise
        the “Last updated” date above. Your continued use of our website or
        services after a change means you accept the updated policy.
      </p>

      <h2>Contact</h2>
      <p>
        Questions about this policy, or want to make a privacy request? Contact
        {business.legalName} at <a href={business.emailHref}>{business.email}</a>
        or {business.phoneDisplay}.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
